<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Hingis Happy Williams Sisters Gone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARIS (AP) -- Martina Hingis was not looking forward to playing  
either of the two Williams sisters in the French Open. To ensure 
success in her draw, Hingis lit a candle at the Sacre Coeur church 
in Paris. 
</P>
<P>
	After Venus Williams lost Sunday to qualifier Barbara Schwartz,  
Hingis said it had been a good idea. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think the candle I lit at Sacre Coeur helped,'' she said.  
``(In the church) you have to pay how much you want, then you can 
take a big candle or a small one,'' said a smiling Hingis. ``I took 
the middle.'' 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	SPORTS FANS: Tennis players look to other sports for  
entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
	One player, Marcelo Fillipini, showed an interest the French  
Rugby league final on Saturday at the Stade de France. The 
Uruguayan player had to cancel, though. 
</P>
<P>
	Against his expectations, Fillipini made it to the fourth round  
of the men's draw. Fillipini thought a good night sleep was more 
important than the rugby final. 
</P>
<P>
	Soccer has proven a more popular sport than rugby in the tennis  
crowd. About a hundred players requested tickets for the Parc des 
Princes soccer stadium to see the last match of the French first 
division between Paris Saint-Germain and Bordeaux. Unfortunately 
for the tennis players, the stadium was sold out. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	SCHOOL'S OUT: For some people it's hard to believe 20-year-old  
Barbara Schwartz is doing so well. At a time when women players 
start earlier and earlier, late developers are rare. Especially if 
you take time off to go to school. 
</P>
<P>
	The Austrian who took out No. 5-seeded Venus Williams Sunday  
said she had more time to practice this year because she had 
finished school. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think it was very important for me, because now I have  
something else besides tennis,'' said Schwartz. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's also good because now I can concentrate on tennis,'' she  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	On Sunday, the extra work paid off when she came back after  
facing three match points to defeat Williams. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	SOCCER STAR: Just as tennis players like soccer, soccer players  
like to watch tennis. 
</P>
<P>
	On Saturday, Zinedine Zidane, the playmaker for Italian power  
Juventus and the French national team, sneaked a peek at the play 
on Suzanne Lenglen court from the photographers' pit. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm duly impressed by the speed and the power of the  
strokes,'' he said. ``I was happy to see some of the games from the 
photographers pit, because there I could really see the 
trajectory.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
