<HEADLINE> Some Major Railroad Mergers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Some of the major railroad mergers in recent years:  
</P>
<P>
	--CSX Corp. and Norfolk Southern Corp. with Conrail Inc.,  
approved in 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	--Union Pacific Corp. with Southern Pacific Rail Corp., approved  
in 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	--Burlington Northern Inc. with Santa Fe Pacific Corp., approved  
in 1995. 
</P>
<P>
	--Union Pacific with Chicago &AMP; North Western Transportation Co.,  
approved in 1995. 
</P>
<P>
	--Denver &AMP; Rio Grande Western Railroad Co. with Southern Pacific,  
approved in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
	--Union Pacific with Missouri-Kansas-Texas Railroad Co., approved  
in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
                            	 *------	 
</P>
<P>
	Source: Surface Transportation Board  

</P>
