<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Couric Speaks at Lehigh University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- You know Katie Couric as the cheerful host  
of NBC's ``Today'' show. Now meet Katie Couric, ABC flunky. 
</P>
<P>
	Couric, speaking at a college commencement at Lehigh University  
on Sunday, recalled her days of getting ham sandwiches for the 
executive producer of ``World News Tonight'' and making photocopies 
for Sam Donaldson. 
</P>
<P>
	Not that she's complaining: Couric advised the graduates to make  
the most of starting at the bottom. 
</P>
<P>
	``Ask questions, be an eager beaver, be Eddie Haskell with  
sincerity,'' she said. 
</P>
<P>
	Couric said finding the right job takes the kind of persistence  
displayed by Lehigh's senior class officers, ``who just wouldn't 
get off my back'' in persuading her to speak. 
</P>
<P>
	Couric turned down 12 commencement invitations this year, but  
said yes to Lehigh after the senior class officers wrote letters, 
camped outside the ``Today'' show, and kept ``begging, pleading and 
stroking my ego, until finally, they just wore me down.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
