<HEADLINE> Ex-Menudo Member Talks to TV Guide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Former members of Menudo shouldn't knock the  
Latin teen group, says Ricky Martin, an alumnus of the band. 
</P>
<P>
	``Yes, it was a boy band,'' Martin told the June 5 issue of TV  
Guide. ``Everything, they tell you what to do.'' 
</P>
<P>
	But he wanted to remind those who still complain about the  
experience: ``Dude, you were sitting under the Eiffel Tower when 
you were 12 years old, and kids in your classroom were reading 
about it. Complaining is for losers.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Martin, 27, is riding high these days with his self-titled  
English-language debut. ``Livin' la Vida Loca,'' the album's first 
single, is topping the music charts, and he is on People magazine's 
list of the 50 ``most beautiful people in the world'' for 1999. 
</P>
<P>
	As he cultivates his sexy image, Martin also is on a spiritual  
quest. So far, he has explored Catholicism, Scientology, Judaism, 
Hinduism and currently, Buddhism. 
</P>
<P>
	``I will always search,'' he said.  
  	   	
</P>
