<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Rise in Early Trading / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- The dollar was higher against the yen early Monday  
as investors covered short, or oversold positions. Tokyo stocks 
rose moderately. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar bought 121.66 yen in early trading, up 1.14 yen from  
late Friday in Tokyo and also above its late New York level of 
121.43 yen, also on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average rose 50.08 points,  
or 0.31 percent, to 16,022.76 in the first 30 minutes of trading. 
On Friday, the average shed 204.51 points, or 1.26 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	In currency dealings, the dollar moved higher on short-covering  
while strength in the euro against the yen also indirectly helped 
support the greenback in relation to the Japanese currency. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro's strength was based on speculation the European  
Central bank may finally move to prop up the euro by intervening in 
foreign exchange markets to buy it. 
</P>
<P>
	So far, no such action by the bank has been seen to try to stem  
the euro's steady decline since its January launch. 
</P>
<P>
	Trading was expected to remain quiet in Tokyo as U.S. and  
European markets are closed Monday for holidays. 
</P>
<P>
	On the stock market, share prices were slightly higher early  
Monday as investors remained nervous over the outlook for recently 
volatile New York financial markets. 
</P>
<P>
	Market sentiment was also hurt by news that foreign investors  
turned into net sellers of Japanese stocks in the week ended May 21 
for the first time in 18 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	``Tokyo stocks are currently linked closely with the performance  
of the U.S. market, and players remain cautious before Friday's key 
U.S. jobs data,'' said a general manager at a Japanese securities 
company, speaking on condition of anonymity. 
</P>
<P>
	The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the  
first section was up 5.80 points, or 0.45 percent, to 1,297.87. The 
TOPIX closed down 10.10 points, or 0.78 percent, on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	In New York, the Dow Jones industrial average rose 92.81 points  
to close Friday at 10,559.74. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield on the benchmark No. 213 10-year Japanese government  
bond rose to 1.5050 percent from Friday's finish of 1.4900 percent, 
driving its price down to 99.08 yen from 99.21 yen. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
