<DOCNO> APW19990530.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-30 06:11:20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dancers Try for Largest Chorus Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DODGE CITY, Kan. (AP) -- Hundreds of dancers filled a downtown  
street in an attempt to form the world's largest cancan line. 
</P>
<P>
	A piano player cranked out traditional French cancan music on  
Friday night as cattle trucks slowed on nearby Wyatt Earp 
Boulevard, their drivers watching the interlocked dancers kick 
left, then right. 
</P>
<P>
	Organizers said at least 600 men and women attempted to break  
the world record for the number of people to perform the feat 
during the start of the town's annual Cowboy Heritage Festival. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials with the Guinness Book of World Records will review a  
videotape of Friday's event before ruling. 
</P>
<P>
	The nearest official record recognized by Guinness is for the  
world's largest chorus line, set in 1990 in Great Britain by 598 
participants. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think we know now that everybody wants to be a cancan girl,  
at least a little bit,'' said Sonya Hughes, who thought of the 
idea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
