<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Cast of Sitcom Talks to Magazine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Monica and Chandler weren't supposed to fall in  
love. 
</P>
<P>
	The producers of the top-rated sitcom ``Friends'' originally  
conceived a ``dark horse'' romance between Monica, played by 
Courtney Cox, and Joey, played by Matt LeBlanc. 
</P>
<P>
	``This was before we cast the show,'' David Crane told the June  
4 edition of Entertainment Weekly magazine. The creators intended 
this second romance to play off the one between David Schwimmer's 
Ross and Jennifer Aniston's Rachel. 
</P>
<P>
	Ultimately, the producers decided that Monica and Chandler,  
played by Matthew Perry, would make the most strangely entertaining 
bedfellows. ``We've gone out of our way to make it feel different 
than Ross and Rachel,'' said Crane. 
</P>
<P>
	``We didn't do anything to lead up to it,'' he said. ``We  
thought it could be one episode or three, but they have so many 
problems built into their characters that it's yielded a ton of 
wonderful stories.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
