<HEADLINE> Al Michaels Talks to TV Guide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Al Michaels says losing his longtime ``Monday  
Night Football'' broadcast partners, Frank Gifford and Dan 
Dierdorf, has been emotional. 
</P>
<P>
	``For me, the changes are personally tough,'' he told the June 5  
issue of TV Guide. ``When you have a long-standing relationship, 
which I had with both guys, changes in that regard are not welcome 
probably by any of us.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Boomer Esiason got mixed reviews after replacing Gifford last  
season. Dierdorf left the network in February after failing to mesh 
with Esiason. 
</P>
<P>
	ABC is considering a return to a two-man booth on ``Monday Night  
Football'' for the first time since Michaels teamed with Gifford 13 
years ago. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
