<HEADLINE> Queen Douna Wins Estrapade Stakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Queen Douna led all the way and won the  
$103,390 Estrapade Stakes by five lengths at Hollywood Park today. 
</P>
<P>
	Queen Douna angled in on the first turn, setting the pace inside  
and opened a huge advantage on the backstretch. Queen Douna 
finished the 1 1/2 miles in 2:27. 
</P>
<P>
	Queen Douna, a 6-year-old mare ridden by David Flores, paid  
$22.80, $5.40 and $2.80 in the race for fillies and mares. 
Runner-up Blending Element paid $2.80 and $2.20, while Zante was 
$2.60 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Queen Douna earned $90,000 for a career total of $325,571. It  
was her fifth win in 28 starts. 
  	   	
