<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-30 17:02:01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Swamp Sets Monmouth Park Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OCEANPORT, N.J. (AP) -- Swamp set a Monmouth Park record for 1  
1-16 miles on the turf while winning the $150,000 Jersey Derby 
today. 
</P>
<P>
	The time of 1:40 4-5 took two-fifths off the record set by  
Double Booked in 1989. 
</P>
<P>
	Trained by John Kimmel, Swamp took command around the far turn  
and drew off to a 3 1/4-length victory, returning $3.60 as the 
favorite of a crowd of 15,805. 
</P>
<P>
	``Around the far turn he just dropped his head and took off,''  
said winning rider Richard Migliore. ``This is a serious race 
horse. He really impressed me today.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Crash Course was second, followed by Good Skate.  
</P>
<P>
	The victory was the fourth in six career for Swamp, whose  
earnings grew to $222,240. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
